Romania’s RCS&RDS Seeks $294 Million for Acquisition, ZF Says

-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 
2011-04-27T06:44:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/romania-s-rcs-rds-seeks-294-million-for-acquisition-zf-says.html
RCS&RDS SA, a Romanian
telecommunications company, hired Credit Suisse First Boston PF
Europe Ltd. to help it raise 200 million euros ($294 million)
for a possible acquisition of  Liberty Global Inc. (LBTYA) ’ local unit,
Ziarul Financiar reported today, citing unidentified market
people.  RCS&RDS wants a seven-year loan from international markets
and may use the money to make a bid for competitor, Liberty’s
UPC Romania SA, according to the Bucharest-based news paper.  Ziarul Financiar  reported in March, that Liberty,
controlled by U.S. billionaire  John Malone , might sell UPC
Romania, after the company started losing market share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez in Prague at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  